Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on radio access management in cellular networks, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a grant-free narrowband data transmission protocol, which involves signal processing and diversity techniques, that can be analyzed using information theory. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The proposed scheme involves complex signal processing at the receiver side, which can be analyzed using systems and control theory. 
4. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper discusses the performance evaluation of the proposed scheme in terms of reliability and battery-lifetime, which are important metrics for multimedia applications. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper does not explicitly discuss security, but the proposed scheme can have implications on the security of the network, as it involves sending multiple replicas of the same packet.
